  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Integrated Modeling of the Land Use, Water and Energy Nexus of Brazilian Biofuels Expansion under Climate Change</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The purpose of the project was to inform decision-makers and stakeholder groups about possible scenarios for the expansion of agrofuels under climate change in Brazil. This included demonstrating potential negative impacts on water resources, land use and food security at an early stage, so as to be able to reduce these impacts in further stages of planning and promote sustainable agrofuel production. The project&apos;s work therefore focused on modelling possible impacts on water resources, land use, social and economic development and greenhouse gas emissions. Quantitative analysis was supported by a stakeholder process, which served to integrate expert knowledge and to distribute project results.</narrative>
  </description>
